    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Style of painting that  flourished in Italy and northern Europe for three decades after the death of Michelangelo Caravaggio (1571-1610). The style was strongly influenced by Caravaggio’s use of everyday, common or lower class scenes and figures; the style employed the lighting effects of tenebrism (figures and objects in a dark background, with some details picked out as strongly lit from a single light source).</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
